==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: kepi
<hw>kep"i</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>k⟦eacute⟧pi</ets>, of G. origin.]</ety> <def>A military cap having
a close-fitting band, a round flat top sloping toward the front, and a
visor. As originally worn by the French in Algeria about 1830 it was
tall and stiff with a straight visor. It is now lower, has a curved
visor, and is frequently soft.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> peaked cap, service cap, yachting cap.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>kept</ent>⟦br⟧
